securityDepositClause73: If the Lessor intends to sell the Leased Premises or assign all rights under this Lease Deed to a third party ("New Lessor"), such transfer shall require the prior written consent of the Lessee. Upon consent, the security deposit shall be transferred to the New Lessor, and the Lessor shall be relieved of liability for its return.
terminationClause201: The Lessor shall have the right to terminate the lease in the event of a default by the Lessee. The Lessor must first provide a written notice to the Lessee specifying the nature of the default. If the Lessee fails to remedy the default within 7 days of receiving such notice, the Lessor may proceed with termination by serving a final termination notice.
terminationClause202: Upon any termination of the Lease for any reason, the Lessee shall return physical vacant possession of the scheduled property to the Lessor within 5 days of termination notice, concurrently with the Lessor refunding the Security Deposit to the Lessee after deducting all amounts due and payable by the Lessee under this Lease Deed. Either party may terminate this lease before the expiration of the Lease Period by providing 30 days written notice to the other party and paying a penalty equivalent to 500.
assignmentClause23: The Lessor shall have the right to sell, assign, convey, or transfer his interest in the Leased Premises or his rights and obligations under this Lease Deed to any third party without obtaining the written consent of the Lessee, provided that he ensures the prospective purchaser/assignee agrees to be bound by the terms of this Lease Deed. The assignee's business activities must be compatible with the nature and purpose of the Leased Premises. Upon assignment, the original Lessor shall remain jointly liable with the assignee for all obligations under this Lease Deed until the lease expiry or early termination.
mortgageClause26: Lessor reserves the right to mortgage or otherwise place a lien on the Leased Premises. However, the Lessor must provide the Lessee with nfhirnmckncmc of any such mortgage or lien.
